{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"88d02f8d-0366-43e3-983c-57ef8085e29c","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01FgYY9SnAULNj5eo1DrsdjQ","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017oEsAAigUWpeVeLayovQzg","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-3f688152a88d46f2a2e57535ae7df86d/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <!-- MSTest v3 settings (replaces .testsettings) -->\n  <MSTest>\n    <!-- Default timeout for all test methods (ms) -->\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n    <!-- DeploymentEnabled replaces the old AssemblyResolution/TestDirectory config.\n         Set to false because MSTest v3 runs tests in-place by default. -->\n    <DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>\n  </MSTest>\n\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n                     uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n                     assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral\">\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-3f688152a88d46f2a2e57535ae7df86d/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"30673819-2897-44cb-a065-00445974137d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file with:\n1. Assembly resolution / test deployment config\n2. A test timeout of 30000ms (30 seconds)\n3. A code coverage data collector\n\nIn MSTest v3, `.testsettings` files are no longer supported. The configuration needs to be migrated to a `.runsettings` file and/or MSTest v3 attributes/properties.\n\nLet me explain how to migrate each setting:\n\n1. **Test timeout** → Use `[Timeout]` attribute on test methods, or set a default timeout in `.runsettings` via MSTest settings.\n\n\n2. **Code coverage data collector** → Configure in `.runsettings` file under `<DataCollectors>`.\n3. **Assembly resolution / deployment** → MSTest v3 handles deployment differently; the `useLoadContext` setting is the default behavior.\n\nNow I'll create a `.runsettings` file that replaces the `.testsettings` configuration.","outputTokens":637,"requestId":"0419:3CBAC0:15C0D87:172EF59:6A033769"},"id":"1dfe1610-eff0-4813-97a0-73802dff3ed8","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:21:40.692Z","parentId":"99624b4d-a296-4eb6-ac62-43517789bd8c"}
