{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1d1b6c11-efb0-4c77-91d3-3c4d10ca0357","content":"Here's a summary of the migration:\n\n### `.testsettings` → `.runsettings` mapping\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `<Property name=\"TestTimeout\" value=\"30000\" />` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout></MSTest>` |\n| `<TestDirectory useLoadContext=\"true\" />` | `<MSTest><DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled></MSTest>` (MSTest v3 runs in-place by default) |\n| Code coverage `DataCollector` in `<AgentRule>` | `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>` at the top level |\n\n### What changed\n1. **Created `local.runsettings`** — the MSTest v3 replacement for `.testsettings`.\n2. **Updated `TestProject.csproj`** — added `<RunSettingsFilePath>` so the runsettings file is picked up automatically.\n3. **`local.testsettings`** — can now be deleted; MSTest v3 ignores it entirely.\n\nYou can also pass the runsettings on the CLI: `dotnet test --settings local.runsettings`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"30673819-2897-44cb-a065-00445974137d","outputTokens":298,"requestId":"040F:13FE50:15EA4BB:17598B5:6A033779"},"id":"06349ca5-c3c2-4f0a-abcf-947357faec9e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:21:54.241Z","parentId":"7c483596-795e-4e85-9f52-5d0ff4674088"}
